content:
OmniScript Setup Reference

Default Setup Properties

* Console Tab Icon: Applies an icon to the console tab where the OmniScript is embedded.
* Console Tab Title: Applies text to the console tab where the OmniScript is embedded.
* Currency Code: Override the default currency by configuring the currency code field.
* Reusable: Enables the OmniScript to be embedded into another OmniScript when checked.
* Element Type To LWC Component Mapping: Enables a custom Lightning web component to override all elements of a specific Element Type.
* Enable SEO: Make your OmniScript's URL available to search engines.
* Enable Unload Warning: Triggers a Leave Site? warning when reloading, navigating away, or closing the window.
* Fetch Picklist Values At Script Load: Enables picklist values to be retrieved at script load when selected.
* Enable Logging Metrics: Sends data to Salesforce about which OmniScript elements are used at runtime.
* Enable Logging Metrics for Hidden Actions and Steps: Sends data to Salesforce about which OmniScript hidden actions and steps are used at runtime.
* Lightning Web Component: The target custom Lightning web component that you map to your Element Type.
* Seed Data JSON: Enables the OmniScript to be seeded with data on launch.
* Tracking Custom Data: Log custom data to the Vlocity Tracking Entry table by adding Key/Value pairs.

Setup Property Sections

* Step Chart Options: Hide or move an OmniScript's Step Chart using Step Chart Options.
* Cancel Options: Navigate users to different Salesforce experiences after canceling an OmniScript by configuring cancel options.
* Save Options: Enable users to save and resume OmniScripts by using OmniScript's Save Options property.
* Knowledge Options: Enable users to search and view Salesforce Knowledge Articles when using an OmniScript.
* Error Messages: Set a default error message or simplify error messages for users.

Configure an OmniScript's Currency Code
Override an org's default currency in an OmniScript by setting the OmniScript's Currency Code.

Step Chart Options
Hide or move an OmniScript's Step Chart using Step Chart Options.

Configure OmniScript Cancel Options
Navigate users to different Salesforce experiences after canceling an OmniScript by configuring cancel options.

Save and Resume an OmniScript
Enable users to save and resume OmniScripts by using OmniScript's Save Options property.
